<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>

<worksheet xml:id="app3-reading" xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude">
    <title>APP-3 Reading</title>
    <objectives>
    <ul>
      <li><p>Things you should understand and know:
        <ul>
            <li>Determine divergence for a given vector field</li>
            <li>Determine curl for a given vector field</li>
            <li>Recognize parametric representations of cylinders, cones, and spheres</li>
            <li>The meaning of an oriented surface</li>
        </ul></p>
        <p>Things you should be able to do:
        <ul>
            <li>Use the properties of curl to determine whether a vector field is conservative</li>
            <li>Use the properties of divergence to determine whether a vector field is conservative</li>
            <li>Use a surface integral to calculate the area of a given surface</li>
            <li>Use surface integrals to solve applied problems</li>
        </ul></p>
      </li>
      <li><p>You will be assessed on the following criteria:
        <ul>
          <li><p>Problem structure: Solution should be organized and easy to follow, with clear, complete steps 
              that follow progressively from one to the next.</p></li>
          <li><p>Divergence and Curl: Be able to calculate the divergence and curl for a vector field. Use 
            the divergence and curl to evaluate integrals.</p></li>
            <li><p>Surface Integrals: Be able to parameterize a surface. Be able to orient a surface. Calculate 
                surface integrals of scalar and vector fields. Use surface integrals to solve applied problems</p></li>
        </ul></p>
      </li>
    </ul>
    </objectives>
        <p>All of the readings for this course come from the OpenStax Calculus 
            Volume 3 textbook, which is available for free online at 
            <url href="https://openstax.org/details/books/calculus-volume-3">
                https://openstax.org/details/books/calculus-volume-3</url>. You 
                can read the textbook online or download a PDF version. 
                The textbook is also available in print from various retailers 
                if you prefer a physical copy.</p> 
        <p>For this lesson, you should read sections <url href="https://openstax.org/books/calculus-volume-3/pages/6-5-divergence-and-curl">
            6.5 Divergence and Curl</url> and <url href="https://openstax.org/books/calculus-volume-3/pages/6-6-surface-integrals">
            6.6 Surface Integrals</url>. You should read through the sections carefully, 
            making sure to understand the definitions, examples, and key ideas. 
            You should also work through the exercises at the end of each section 
            to test your understanding and practice applying the concepts. Some of the 
            exercises at the end of the section are assigned in the WP assignments.</p>      
</worksheet>
